6 (b) A water provider may replace a lead service line located on
7 private property if the water provider:
8 (1) Obtains the consent of the owner of the private property
9 where the lead service line is located; and
10 (2) Complies with local regulations and policies that govern the
11 water provider.
12 (c) A water provider may:
13 (1) Spend water utility rate revenue and other public moneys,
